      • scanAndRegister

        <S> void scanAndRegister(S source)
        Scans the source object for any fields/methods that have been annotated with Probe annotation, and registers these fields/methods as probe instances.

        If a probe with the same name already exists, the probe is overwritten silently.

        If an object has no @Probe annotations, the call is ignored.

        Parameters:
        source - the object to scan
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the source contains Probe annotation on a field/method of unsupported type.
